article.headline: Cornell 76, Dartmouth 53
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Andrew Naeve had 21 points and five rebounds to lead Cornell to a 76-53 victory over Dartmouth in the Ivy League on Saturday. Cornell (16-12, 9-5 Ivy) shot 51 percent from the floor and limited Dartmouth (9-18, 5-9) to 37 percent shooting. Cornell scored the first two points and never trailed, completing a season sweep of the Big Green. Freshman Louis Dale had 16 points and a career-high 12 rebounds for Cornell. Ryan Wittman added 14 points. Dan Biber scored 14 points to lead Dartmouth, while DeVon Mosley added 10. Dartmouth made 12-of-13 free throws but was outrebounded 39-21.
